article.headline: UC Irvine 68, UC Davis 48
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. (AP) -- Freshman Michael Hunter scored 16 of his 18 points in the second half to help UC Irvine beat UC Davis 68-48 Saturday night. Chuma Awaji had 16 points, seven rebounds, three assists and two steals for the Anteaters (6-8), who won their first game on the road in eight tries. Behind 18-10, the Anteaters went on a 15-4 run to lead 25-22 at the half. UC Irvine was 11-for-15 from the free-throw line in the first half. The Aggies led 28-27 early in the second half before allowing UC Irvine to stage a 30-11 run in 11 minutes to take a 57-37 lead with 5:46 left to play. The Anteaters also held UC Davis to two field goals in the last 12:19. Thomas Juillerat had 14 points to lead UC Davis (1-10).
